## The Right Architecture: One Oracle, Full Context

### Why per-card LLM is wrong
```
Card click → LLM sees 1 data point
Card click → LLM sees 1 data point   ← 20 clicks, 20 isolated windows
Card click → LLM sees 1 data point
```
No LLM ever synthesizes: "ADP miss + GDP miss + Kill Chain RED + COT specs short = risk-off"

### The correct flow
```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  useMasterBrief()  →  MasterBrief (11 keys) │  real data, no mocks
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  useOracleBrief(masterData)                 │  ONE Groq call
│  → POST /api/v1/oracle/brief                │  full payload, no vibe-coding
│  → OracleBrief (verdict + sections + impl) │
└────────────────────┬────────────────────────┘
                     │
                     ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│  OracleContext.Provider                     │  distributes to all panels
│  → OracleBriefStrip (always visible)       │  no clicks
│  → TacticalSection  (HH + Deriv + KC)      │  reads oracle slice
│  → PreSignalSection (ADP + GDP + Jobless)  │  reads oracle slice
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

