        },
    }
```

#### Oracle Response Shape

```json
{
  "verdict": "one sentence — cross-signal synthesis",
  "risk_level": "HIGH | MEDIUM | LOW | UNKNOWN",
  "sections": {
    "pre_signal":   { "summary": "1-2 sentences", "confidence": 0.76 },
    "hidden_hands": { "summary": "1-2 sentences", "confidence": 0.64 },
    "derivatives":  { "summary": "1-2 sentences", "confidence": 0.81 },
    "kill_chain":   { "summary": "1-2 sentences", "confidence": 0.72 },
    "regime":       { "summary": "1-2 sentences", "confidence": 0.69 }
  },
  "trade_implication": "one sentence action",
  "generated_at": "ISO_TIMESTAMP",
  "cached_until": "ISO_TIMESTAMP"
}
```

#### Fallback (Groq down or timeout)

```json
{ "verdict": "UNAVAILABLE", "risk_level": "UNKNOWN", "sections": {}, "trade_implication": null }
```
> Frontend hides OracleBriefStrip when `risk_level === "UNKNOWN"`. Never show stale guidance.

#### Guardrails in System Prompt

```
Rules Oracle must follow:
1. Do NOT override discrete signals. If kill_chain layer_3 triggered=false, do not say all 3 firing.
2. You may only: summarize confluence, highlight contradictions, map to trade implications.
3. Each section summary: 2 sentences max. No filler words.
4. confidence = 0.0-1.0 signal agreement strength (not LLM certainty).
5. Output strict JSON only.
```

